        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 2 at 4:55PM MDT until August 2 at 5:15PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 455 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles southeast
of Mount Dora, or 14 miles west of Clayton, moving southeast at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Central Union County.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
